{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-00235/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-00235"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:02:35"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["full shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, tracking, tilt"]}},{"label":{"none":["Lighting"]},"value":{"none":["high key"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["group shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["Women ascend a spiral staircase."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00235/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-00235","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00235/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-00235"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00235/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00235/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00235/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00235/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00235/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00235/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00235/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00235/canvas/1/eb32c451-f673-4391-ab29-8157079bde1a","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T14:33:28.783Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The film was largely shot on-location in a five-story townhouse on Fitzroy Square in central London in December 2016 and April 2017. The townhouse as filming location echoed its onscreen counterpart as a bustling hub of production. Despite the house’s ostensible size—eight reception rooms, seven bedrooms, and seven bathrooms—the cast and crew frequently found themselves in tight quarters. Film equipment exceeded the storage space afforded by the basement and back rooms and had to be shuttled around rooms between scenes. Daniel Day-Lewis lamented that “the entire house was like a termite nest,” while Vicky Krieps noted that it felt akin to the small-budget independent films she was used to working on. Only Lesley Manville characterized 3 Fitzroy Square as “a huge, huge house” (Vincent, “Daniel Day-Lewis slept here”). PTA and the cast speak about the challenges of working in these tight, beautiful quarters <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW94767885 BCX0\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WGqq7PRpORM\"><u>here</u></a>.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00235/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:400.970802919708,268.79562043795625,510.63503649635044,783.8430656934307"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00235/canvas/1/67cccc8b-6074-406e-81cf-0cdcf38ccdb7","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T14:33:41.615Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>As the dressmakers walk into the Woodcock estate, we see winding staircases and narrow, curving halls. These physical characteristics of the house emulate Reynolds’ personality. The thin, narrow halls and steep, curved stairways show the viewer that Reynolds is particular and complex, someone that needs to be learned.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00235/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:952.7299270072992,113.0912408759124,283.64233576642346,928.9927007299272"}}}]}]}]}